---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "Kenmore Appliance Repair | Southern California | Elite, Pro, OEM Decode";
const description = "Kenmore repair across Southern California — Elite + Pro + standard tiers across Whirlpool, Frigidaire, LG, Samsung, GE OEM chassis. Model-number prefix decoding. $89 diagnostic. (424) 325-0520.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/kenmore/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is Kenmore a manufacturer or a brand?",
    a: "Kenmore is a <b>retailer brand</b>, not a manufacturer — a critical distinction that affects every Kenmore service call. Sears launched the Kenmore brand in 1927 and contracted manufacturing from various OEMs across the decades: Whirlpool, Frigidaire (when owned by various parents), LG, Samsung, GE, and others have built Kenmore-branded products in specific product categories + specific eras. Sears owned the Kenmore brand through its 2018 bankruptcy; Transformco acquired it 2018-2022; Transform Holdco operates the brand from 2022 onward. <b>Because Kenmore is a retailer brand, no single OEM builds all Kenmore units</b>. Your Kenmore refrigerator might be built by Whirlpool, your Kenmore range by Frigidaire, your Kenmore washer by LG — all under the Kenmore marketing umbrella. For service, this means the real question isn't 'how do I fix a Kenmore oven' but 'which OEM built THIS specific Kenmore oven, and what's that OEM's parts-chain + diagnostic approach'. The model-number prefix decodes which."
  },
  {
    q: "How do I decode which OEM built my Kenmore?",
    a: "Model number starts with a 3-digit prefix that identifies the manufacturer. Check the Model # on the inside-door trim plate or rear label — a 3-digit prefix precedes the rest of the model number. Common Kenmore OEM prefixes: <b>110</b> = Whirlpool (most common historical Kenmore OEM across refrigerators, washers, dryers, some ovens); <b>253</b> = Frigidaire/Electrolux (refrigerators, ovens, ranges, AC); <b>665</b> = Whirlpool (dishwashers specifically); <b>795</b> = LG (many 2010s+ refrigerators, laundry); <b>401</b> = Samsung (some 2010s+ refrigerators, laundry); <b>362</b> = GE Appliances (appliances from GE-built Kenmore era); <b>106</b> = Whirlpool (older refrigerator specific); <b>790</b> = LG (mid-2010s); <b>417</b> = Frigidaire (laundry specific). There are additional + legacy prefixes — our service tablets carry the full decoder. At diagnostic, prefix identification is step 1: it tells us which parts chain applies, which diagnostic approach to use, and which cross-reference catalogs to source."
  },
  {
    q: "Sears went bankrupt — does Kenmore parts still exist?",
    a: "Yes, parts exist — but the service channel changed fundamentally. Sears' 2018 bankruptcy eliminated the Sears Home Services dispatch + the authorized Sears Kenmore service network. Parts themselves come from the original OEMs (Whirlpool, Frigidaire, LG, Samsung, GE) who built your Kenmore unit, which is why <b>model-number prefix decoding is the entry point for service post-2018</b>. A Kenmore oven with 253 prefix (Frigidaire) gets serviced with Frigidaire parts through Frigidaire's parts-chain; a Kenmore oven with 110 prefix (Whirlpool) gets serviced with Whirlpool parts. Parts availability is generally good for Kenmore units up to 15-20 years depending on OEM; older Kenmore (pre-2000) sometimes requires aftermarket cross-reference. Transform Holdco (current Kenmore brand owner) sells new Kenmore-branded products online + through appliance retailers but doesn't operate service dispatch."
  },
  {
    q: "What are Kenmore Elite + Kenmore Pro tiers?",
    a: "Kenmore tiered its product line similarly to GE's Mainstream/Profile/Café hierarchy. <b>Kenmore (standard)</b> — entry + mid tier, most common in older Sears-era households, simpler trim + controls. <b>Kenmore Elite</b> — premium tier, feature-rich with touch controls + smart features + better finishes, often built by LG or Samsung in the Elite era. <b>Kenmore Pro</b> — commercial-style prosumer tier, pro-style ranges + larger capacity built-ins, typically built by Electrolux or Whirlpool premium divisions; positioned against Viking/Wolf at lower price. Tier matters for service: Elite Series parts generally still stocked through OEM channels (LG, Samsung parts-chain); Pro parts may route through specialty OEM channels with longer lead. Most current LA Kenmore service is Elite + standard tiers in 2005-2018 production. Pro tier is less common in our service volume but still serviceable when we can identify the OEM prefix."
  },
  {
    q: "Should I keep my Kenmore or replace after Sears closed?",
    a: "Repair-vs-replace on Kenmore depends heavily on OEM + age + specific failure. <b>Keep + repair case</b>: Kenmore with Whirlpool (110), Frigidaire (253), or LG (795) prefix at 5-12 year age with single-component failure. Parts available through OEM, repair economics reasonable, unit has remaining service life. <b>Borderline case</b>: 12-18 year Kenmore with control-board failure — parts lead time may run 2-3 weeks on older OEM-chassis boards, repair cost approaches replacement. <b>Replacement lean</b>: 20+ year Kenmore regardless of OEM — aftermarket cross-reference required for many parts, multiple near-term failures likely. <b>Loyalty-emotional case</b>: grandmother's Kenmore that still works mechanically — repair cosmetic wear + honor the sentimental value, but we flag honestly when economic repair makes less sense than replacement. Our approach at diagnostic: OEM identification + age + failure assessment + honest repair-vs-replace guidance, no pressure either direction."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you service Kenmore Pro commercial-style ranges?",
    a: "Yes — Kenmore Pro service is within our residential scope despite the 'Pro' branding. Kenmore Pro is prosumer-tier (residential-use but commercial-styled), NOT true commercial-spec equipment. Kenmore Pro ranges, built-in refrigerators, and larger-capacity built-ins were positioned against Viking / Wolf / Thermador at lower retail price point. OEM identification same approach — model-number prefix decodes which manufacturer built the Pro unit. Parts-chain runs through that OEM's premium channel (Electrolux Icon, Whirlpool premium, Frigidaire Professional depending on era). Service economics on Kenmore Pro run higher than standard Kenmore (pro-style parts cost more), lower than equivalent-tier Viking/Wolf (volume-manufacture pro parts vs small-batch luxury parts). Most LA Kenmore Pro installations are 2005-2015 luxury-adjacent remodels where owners wanted pro-style aesthetic without Viking/Wolf pricing."
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "LocalBusiness", "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair — Kenmore Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical, "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL, "priceRange": "$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Organization", "@id": canonical + "#brand",
    "name": "Kenmore", "url": canonical, "description": "Retailer brand operated by Transform Holdco (formerly Sears). Units manufactured by various OEMs — Whirlpool, Frigidaire, LG, Samsung, GE — identified by model-number prefix. Post-Sears-bankruptcy service requires OEM identification for parts-chain routing."
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } })) },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Kenmore", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">{schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}</Fragment>
  <div class="call-banner"><div class="wrap"><span>Kenmore service? Same-day across LA:</span><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a></div></div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › Kenmore</div>
    <h1>Kenmore Appliance Repair</h1>
    <p class="lede">Kenmore is the Sears-legacy retailer brand now owned by Transform Holdco, serviced in LA through our <b>model-number prefix OEM decoding</b> approach — the correct diagnostic entry point post-Sears-bankruptcy. Your Kenmore oven, refrigerator, washer, or dishwasher was built by one of several OEMs (Whirlpool, Frigidaire, LG, Samsung, GE) — model prefix identifies which, which determines parts-chain routing and diagnostic approach. Our LA Kenmore service handles <b>Elite Series</b> (premium), <b>Pro Series</b> (commercial-style prosumer), and <b>standard</b> Kenmore across all appliance categories with OEM-specific parts sourcing. Sears-loyal LA households span Pasadena, Long Beach, San Fernando Valley, and older LA residential neighborhoods where Kenmore was the trusted household-appliance default for decades. Same-day dispatch. Residential diagnostic $89, waived with repair.</p>
    <div class="hero-cta"><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a><a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a></div>
    <ul class="hero-facts">
      <li><b>Retailer brand, NOT manufacturer</b> — OEM decoding is step 1</li>
      <li><b>Model-number prefix decoder</b> — 110 Whirlpool / 253 Frigidaire / 795 LG / 401 Samsung / 362 GE</li>
      <li><b>Post-Sears-bankruptcy service</b> — parts via OEM, not Sears channel</li>
      <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b> — waived when you authorize the repair</li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>CSLB #1138898 · Insured</span><span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span><span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Kenmore OEM prefix decoder — what built your Kenmore</h2>
    <p>Every Kenmore appliance starts with a 3-digit OEM prefix on its model number. That prefix is the <b>entry point for service</b> — it tells us which manufacturer built the unit, which determines the parts chain, diagnostic approach, and realistic repair economics. Locate the Model # on interior door trim plate (oven, refrigerator, dishwasher) or rear panel label (washer, dryer).</p>
    <table class="price-table">
      <tr><th>Prefix</th><th>OEM</th><th>Product notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td><b>110</b></td><td>Whirlpool</td><td>Historical Kenmore OEM — refrigerators, washers, dryers, some ovens + ranges. Broadest parts-chain availability through Whirlpool USA.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><b>253</b></td><td>Frigidaire / Electrolux</td><td>Refrigerators, ovens, ranges, AC. Parts chain through Electrolux USA.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><b>665</b></td><td>Whirlpool (dishwashers)</td><td>Dishwasher-specific Whirlpool Kenmore prefix. Same parts-chain as 110.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><b>795</b></td><td>LG</td><td>Mid-2010s+ refrigerators + laundry. LG USA parts chain.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><b>790</b></td><td>LG (mid-2010s)</td><td>LG earlier-generation Kenmore.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><b>401</b></td><td>Samsung</td><td>Some 2010s+ refrigerators + laundry. Samsung parts chain.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><b>362</b></td><td>GE Appliances</td><td>GE-built Kenmore era (historical). GE parts chain.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><b>106</b></td><td>Whirlpool (older refrigerator)</td><td>Older refrigerator-specific Whirlpool Kenmore.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><b>417</b></td><td>Frigidaire (laundry)</td><td>Frigidaire-built Kenmore laundry.</td></tr>
    </table>
    <p>Additional + legacy prefixes exist — our service tablets carry the full decoder for older units. Prefix identification is always step 1 at diagnostic.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Kenmore appliance categories we service</h2>
    <div class="cat-grid-simple">
      <a href="/brands/kenmore-oven-repair/" class="cat-card-link">
        <h3>Kenmore oven repair →</h3>
        <p>Elite Series + Pro + standard wall ovens + range-integrated. 106 imp GSC demand. OEM-specific parts sourcing.</p>
      </a>
      <div class="cat-card-link-static">
        <h3>Kenmore refrigerator repair</h3>
        <p>Top-freezer, bottom-freezer, side-by-side, French-door. Mix of Whirlpool, LG, Samsung OEM across tiers.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cat-card-link-static">
        <h3>Kenmore washer + dryer repair</h3>
        <p>Top-loader + front-loader + stackable. Whirlpool + LG + Frigidaire + Samsung OEM across production eras.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cat-card-link-static">
        <h3>Kenmore dishwasher repair</h3>
        <p>Built-in + portable. Whirlpool OEM (665 prefix) across most production, LG on recent Elite.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cat-card-link-static">
        <h3>Kenmore range repair</h3>
        <p>Gas + electric freestanding + slide-in ranges. Frigidaire (253) + Whirlpool (110) majority historical.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cat-card-link-static">
        <h3>Kenmore cooktop + microwave</h3>
        <p>Built-in cooktops + over-range microwaves. OEM depends on era + tier.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>What Sears bankruptcy means for Kenmore service</h2>
    <p>Sears' October 2018 bankruptcy eliminated the Sears Home Services dispatch network + the authorized Sears Kenmore service channel. This created confusion for Kenmore owners who had always called Sears first — suddenly that phone number didn't work, and there was no single "Kenmore service" replacement. The reality underneath: parts + diagnostic knowledge for Kenmore units live with the OEMs who built them, not with the Sears/Transformco brand channel.</p>
    <p>Our approach navigates this cleanly. At diagnostic, we identify OEM via model-number prefix first, then source parts through that OEM's standard residential parts-chain (Whirlpool, Electrolux, LG, Samsung, GE all maintain US parts distribution with LA service). Diagnostic follows that OEM's service patterns — a Kenmore oven with 253 prefix gets Frigidaire-pattern diagnostic (IQ-Touch drift, Luxury-Glide racks, Perfect Temp Conversion are Electrolux-chassis features); a Kenmore oven with 110 prefix gets Whirlpool-pattern diagnostic (AquaLift steam-clean, Scan-to-Cook Wi-Fi, Whirlpool F-codes).</p>
    <p>Current Transform Holdco Kenmore-branded products sold post-2022 still follow the same OEM-built pattern — new Kenmore units come from one of the same OEM pool. Service approach for current + legacy Kenmore is the same: identify OEM, route through OEM parts chain.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>LA neighborhoods — where our Kenmore calls concentrate</h2>
    <div class="area-grid">
      <div><h4>Pasadena + San Gabriel Valley</h4><p><a href="/pasadena/">Pasadena</a> · San Marino · Arcadia · Alhambra · San Gabriel · Temple City — Sears-loyal mid-century households</p></div>
      <div><h4>Long Beach + South Bay</h4><p>Long Beach · Torrance · Lakewood · Bellflower · Cerritos · South Gate</p></div>
      <div><h4>San Fernando Valley</h4><p>Burbank · Glendale · Van Nuys · North Hollywood · Sherman Oaks · Northridge</p></div>
      <div><h4>Mid-LA + South LA</h4><p>Mid-City · Culver City · Mar Vista · Palms · Leimert Park · Crenshaw</p></div>
      <div><h4>Orange County legacy</h4><p><a href="/irvine/">Irvine</a> · Santa Ana · Orange · Fullerton · Anaheim · Garden Grove — OC Sears-loyal households</p></div>
      <div><h4>Inland Empire</h4><p>Ontario · Riverside · Corona · San Bernardino — broader SoCal Kenmore service area</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Related Kenmore and OEM-specific pages</h2>
    <ul class="related-links">
      <li><a href="/brands/kenmore-oven-repair/">Kenmore oven repair →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/whirlpool/">Whirlpool hub (OEM 110 + 665) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/frigidaire/">Frigidaire hub (OEM 253 + 417) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/lg/">LG hub (OEM 795 + 790) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/samsung/">Samsung hub (OEM 401) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/ge/">GE hub (OEM 362) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/services/oven-repair/">Oven repair service hub →</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Kenmore appliance repair — frequently asked</h2>
    {faqs.map(f => (<details class="faq"><summary>{f.q}</summary><p set:html={f.a}></p></details>))}
  </div></section>

  <section id="book" class="cta-bottom"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Kenmore service? Call the branch closest to your home.</h2>
    <p>Same-day appliance repair in Los Angeles, Orange County, Ventura County. Residential diagnostic $89, waived with repair.</p>
  </div></section>
  <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="float-call" aria-label="Call now">☎ Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
</Layout>

<style>
  :root { --red: #C8102E; --black: #0a0a0a; --gray: #f5f5f5; --border: #e2e2e2; --text: #1a1a1a; --muted: #6b6b6b; }
  body { color: var(--text); } .wrap { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; } .wrap.narrow { max-width: 820px; }
  h1 { font-size: 2.4rem; line-height: 1.15; margin: 12px 0 20px; color: var(--black); }
  h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin: 0 0 16px; color: var(--black); }
  h3 { font-size: 1.2rem; margin: 0 0 10px; color: var(--black); }
  h4 { font-size: 1.02rem; margin: 0 0 6px; color: var(--black); }
  p { line-height: 1.65; margin: 0 0 14px; }
  .call-banner { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 10px 0; }
  .call-banner .wrap { display:flex; gap: 14px; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .call-banner .phone-lg { color:#fff; font-weight: 800; text-decoration: underline; font-size: 1.05rem; }
  .hero { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 42px 0 56px; } .hero h1 { color: #fff; }
  .hero .lede { font-size: 1.06rem; color: #d7d7d7; max-width: 680px; }
  .hero .crumb { color: #9a9a9a; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-bottom: 6px; } .hero .crumb a { color: #c9c9c9; text-decoration: none; }
  .hero-cta { display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin: 18px 0 24px; }
  .btn { display: inline-block; padding: 12px 20px; border-radius: 4px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }
  .btn-primary { background: var(--red); color: #fff; } .btn-ghost { background: transparent; color: #fff; border: 1px solid #fff; }
  .hero-facts { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; color: #c9c9c9; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .hero-facts li { padding: 6px 0; border-top: 1px solid #222; } .hero-facts li:first-child { border-top: 0; }
  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 0; }
  .trust-bar .wrap { display: flex; gap: 28px; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 600; }
  .section { padding: 56px 0; } .section.alt { background: var(--gray); }
  .cat-grid-simple { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 18px; margin-top: 20px; }
  .cat-card-link, .cat-card-link-static { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px; border-radius: 6px; display: block; text-decoration: none; color: inherit; transition: all .2s; }
  .cat-card-link:hover { border-color: var(--red); transform: translateY(-2px); }
  .cat-card-link h3, .cat-card-link-static h3 { color: var(--black); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .cat-card-link p, .cat-card-link-static p { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.94rem; margin: 0; }
  .price-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 14px; background: #fff; }
  .price-table th, .price-table td { text-align: left; padding: 11px 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .price-table th { background: var(--black); color: #fff; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .area-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 18px; }
  .area-grid > div { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 16px; border-radius: 6px; }
  .related-links { list-style: none; padding: 0; } .related-links li { padding: 10px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .related-links a { color: var(--red); font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; } .related-links a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .faq { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 12px 16px; margin-bottom: 8px; border-radius: 4px; }
  .faq summary { font-weight: 700; cursor: pointer; padding: 4px 0; } .faq p { margin: 8px 0 0; }
  .cta-bottom { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 48px 0; } .cta-bottom h2 { color: #fff; } .cta-bottom p { color: #c9c9c9; }
  .float-call { position: fixed; bottom: 18px; right: 18px; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 18px; border-radius: 40px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; box-shadow: 0 6px 18px rgba(0,0,0,0.28); z-index: 50; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  @media (max-width: 820px) { h1 { font-size: 1.9rem; } h2 { font-size: 1.45rem; } .float-call { padding: 11px 14px; font-size: 0.88rem; } .trust-bar .wrap { gap: 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; } }
</style>
